req: Specify stateDirectory as
    @Mock(type = MockType.DEFAULT)
    private StateDirectory stateDirectory;

on line 122.
Then you can omit the expectation for stateDirectory.lock(anyObject()).
Note that with a default mock, the tests shouldNotReportOffsetSumsForUnassignedTaskWithoutCheckpoint() and shouldReleaseLockForUnassignedTasksAfterRebalance() fail, because you do not set the expectation that the state dir unlocks some task directories. You should actually set that expectations, right?

